End to end Framework Design Steps

1. Download and Install relevant Java and Eclipse IDE versions

2. Open Eclipse IDE

3. Create a New Maven Project - File -> New -> Other - Maven Project
	3.1 Create a Maven Archetype Project
		3.1.1 About Maven Archetype Catalog -> 
			https://maven.apache.org/archetype/maven-archetype-plugin/specification/archetype-catalog.html
		3.1.2 If no Catalog exists then might need to add/configure one. 
			Archetype Catalog Url -> https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/archetype-catalog.xml, Name -> Remote Catalog
		3.1.3 Select an Archetype -> Catalog (Remote Catalog), Filter (maven-archetype-quickstart), Version (1.4)
		3.1.4 Specify Archetype parameters -> Group Id (com.maven.framework), Artifact Id (TestNG_Hybrid_TutorialsNinja)

4. Add TestNG Library - Right Click -> Build Path -> Add Libraries -> Select TestNG -> Next -> Finish

5. Update Maven Project - Right Click -> Maven -> Update Project -> Select Maven projects & Update Options ->
	Check "TestNG_Hybrid_TutorialsNinja" and "Force Update of Snapshots/Releases"
	
6. Add/Update relevant dependencies with relevant/compatible versions in the pom.xml file.
7. Understand what to Automate? (Real Job)

8. Sample test Cases - (Start with Test Cases)
	Login - With Valid Credentials, Invalid Credentials, InvalidEmailValidPassword, ValidEmailValidPassword, NoCredentials
	Register
	Search

9. Initially Hard-coded data
10. Refine the Code
11. Further refine the code
12. Individually run the test cases
13. Run the test cases together
14. Run all the test cases together using TestNG.xml
	